A woman in her 80s has died and another person injured following an accident involving a coastguard helicopter landing at a hospital. Two members of the public are thought to have been hurt as the helicopter landed at a helipad at Derriford Hospital in Plymouth yesterday. A local woman in her 80s has since died whilst another person is being treated for their injuries and remains in hospital, Devon and Cornwall Police said. The Maritime and Coastguard Agency said the helicopter was flying a patient to hospital at the time of the incident, which a team from the Air Accidents Investigation Branch was investigating. Devon and Cornwall Police has also launched an initial investigation. ‘One person has died and another remains in hospital following an incident that has taken place today on the grounds of Derriford Hospital, involving a HM Coastguard helicopter,’ the force said on Twitter. ‘An initial investigation is being conducted by Devon and Cornwall Police.’ A Department for Transport spokesperson said: ‘Our deepest sympathies go out to those affected by the incident at Derriford Hospital. ‘It would be inappropriate to comment while the incident is investigated by Devon and Cornwall Police and the Air Accidents Investigation Branch.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.